headlines.description: — Paolo Banchero had 22 points, Cole Anthony scored 12 of his 14 points in the second half, and the surging Orlando Magic beat the Charlotte Hornets 101-89 on Tuesday night for their ninth win in 11 games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Paolo Banchero scores 22 points as Magic beat Hornets for ninth win in 11 games

headlines.description: — With every one of Dean Wade's shots that splashed through the net, the Cavaliers got closer to the Celtics and his confidence grew.
headlines.shortLinkText: Dean Wade scores 20 in fourth, Cavs rally to stun Celtics and end Boston's 11-game winning streak

headlines.description: — The Brooklyn Nets were quickly down double digits to a Philadelphia team missing both its All-Stars.
headlines.shortLinkText: Schroder and Finney-Smith each score 20 in Nets' 112-107 win over the short-handed 76ers

headlines.description: — Jimmy Butler took over late, and it was exactly what the Miami Heat needed.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jimmy Butler takes over late, Heat hold off Pistons 118-110 for 11th win in 14 games

events.name: Atlanta Hawks at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Jalen Johnson scored 26 points to lead the Atlanta Hawks to a 116-100 victory over the New York Knicks on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jalen Johnson scores 26 to lead Hawks over Knicks 116-100

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Toronto Raptors

headlines.description: — Trey Murphy III scored a season-high 34 points and the New Orleans Pelicans handed the short-handed Raptors the worst home defeat in franchise history by hammering Toronto 139-98 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Murphy scores season-high 34 points as Pelicans rout short-handed Raptors 139-98

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Houston Rockets

headlines.description: — Alperen Sengun scored a career-high 45 points with a season-best 16 rebounds to lead the Houston Rockets to a 114-101 win over the San Antonio Spurs Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sengun sets career mark with 45 points as Rockets down Spurs 114-101

headlines.description: — Myles Turner scored all 20 of his points in the first half, Tyrese Haliburton had 19 points and 11 assists, and the Indiana Pacers beat the Dallas Mavericks 137-120 on Tuesday night despite Luka Doncic’s fourth consecutive game with a 30-point...
headlines.shortLinkText: Balanced performance by Pacers too much for Doncic and Mavericks in 137-120 win

headlines.description: — Kevin Durant was off the mark with his jumper — until it mattered most.
headlines.shortLinkText: Durant erupts in OT, leads Suns to 117-107 win over Nuggets after blowing 22-point lead
